description:
&lt;p&gt;Due to the promotion of the present post holder we have vacancy for a mental health and think family specialist nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will lead the trusts responses and support around mental health liaising both internally and external to the Trust. As part of the safeguarding team you will also be actively involved in the safeguarding agenda especially where our patients have both mental health and safeguarding issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post entails communicating and working with training and development, partner health and social care services, local safeguarding boards and legal services , it is a highly successful post that offers the post holder opportunities for service and strategic development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Richard Idle –Named Nurse for Safeguarding Adults (previous post holder)&lt;br /&gt;Tina Hymas-Taylor – Head of Safeguarding&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On 01623 622515 extn 3357&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Richard Idle - Named Nurse for Safeguarding Adults&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: richard.idle@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01623 622515 extn 3357/ 6059&lt;/p&gt;
